            <title>[DERBY-2425] ResultSetMetaData.getColumnDisplaySize() returns a negative value for BLOB columns for client </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2425</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;Client getColumnDisplaySize on a BLOB(1G) column returns &lt;br/&gt;
-2147483648&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;embedded returns  2147483647&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In client, the issue is that for binary values it multiplies the length * 2 and this overflows the int range.&lt;br/&gt;
return (int) (2 * sqlLength_&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;column - 1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12364482">DERBY-2425</key>
